## ðŸ§­ Purpose

This policy defines how billing, subscriptions, free trials, overage charges, and refunds are handled on the **Project Athlete 360** platform.  
It ensures **transparency**, **fair use**, and **legal protection** for both the organization and its users.

---

## ðŸ§¾ 1. Subscription Billing

### 1.1 Billing Cycles
- All paid plans renew **automatically** at the end of their billing period (monthly or annually).  
- Billing occurs in **Indian Rupees (â‚¹)** for Indian users, and **USD ($)** for international customers.  
- Invoices and receipts are automatically issued via our payment partners (Stripe/Razorpay).  

### 1.2 Payment Methods
- We accept **credit/debit cards**, **UPI**, and **NetBanking** (via Razorpay/Stripe gateways).  
- Users are responsible for ensuring valid and active payment methods on file.  

### 1.3 Taxes
- Applicable **GST** (Goods & Services Tax) is added to all invoices as per Indian regulations.  
- Business customers can provide **GSTIN** for input credit purposes.  

---

## ðŸ§© 2. Free Trial Policy

### 2.1 Eligibility
- Each **individual and institution** is eligible for **one free trial** per lifetime.  
- Our backend systems enforce this using the **trialAudit.service**, preventing trial reuse across:
  - Email IDs  
  - IPs  
  - Devices  
  - Institutions  

### 2.2 Duration
- Standard trial duration: **14 days** (unless specified otherwise on the signup page).  

### 2.3 Transition After Trial
- Upon expiry, users must **upgrade to a paid plan** to continue using premium features.  
- Data from expired trials is **retained for 30 days** and then securely deleted.

---

## âš™ï¸ 3. Overage & Usage-Based Billing

### 3.1 Overage Definition
Overage occurs when an institution or user exceeds allocated:
- Storage capacity (e.g., GB per plan)
- API or data request quotas
- Athlete or coach seat limits

### 3.2 Detection & Enforcement
- Overage is monitored continuously by the **overage.service.ts** and **planMonitor.worker.ts**.  
- If sustained usage exceeds limits for **>24 hours**, the system may:
  1. Notify via email and dashboard warnings.  
  2. Automatically charge additional usage fees (based on configured overage rates).  
  3. Enforce temporary feature restrictions if payment fails.  

### 3.3 Transparency
All plan limits and overage rates are displayed on:
- [https://projectathlete360.com/pricing](https://projectathlete360.com/pricing)  
- Within the user dashboard â†’ *Billing > Plan Details*

---

## ðŸ’° 4. Refunds

### 4.1 Eligibility for Refund
Refunds are processed only under the following conditions:
1. **Duplicate payment** made in error.  
2. **Technical failure** during billing resulting in unrecognized charge.  
3. **Cancellation within 7 days** of first subscription (applicable only once per user).  

### 4.2 Non-Refundable Situations
- Partial use of subscription after the first 7 days.  
- Downgrade or mid-cycle cancellation.  
- Account suspension due to policy violation.  
- Promotional or discounted purchases.

### 4.3 Processing
- Refunds are handled by the **refund.service.ts**, routed securely via Stripe or Razorpay.  
- Processing time: **5â€“10 business days**, depending on the payment gateway.  
- Users receive email confirmation upon successful refund issuance.

### 4.4 Fraud Prevention
All refund requests undergo automatic eligibility checks and **admin verification** for high-value transactions (> â‚¹5,000).  

---

## ðŸ§  5. Plan Changes & Cancellations

### 5.1 Upgrading
- Upgrades take effect **immediately**, with prorated charges applied.  

### 5.2 Downgrading
- Downgrades take effect **at the end of the billing period**.  
- No credits are issued for unused days in current billing cycle.  

### 5.3 Cancellation
- Users can cancel anytime from **Billing â†’ Manage Plan**.  
- Once canceled, auto-renewal stops, but access remains until plan expiry.  

---

## ðŸ”’ 6. Security & Compliance

- All billing data is handled via **PCI-DSS compliant** gateways.  
- Project Athlete 360 does **not** store full card information on its servers.  
- Refunds and disputes are logged via **audit trails** for compliance verification.  
- Legal oversight by the **Compliance & Data Protection Office** ensures regulatory alignment (RBI + IT Act 2000).

---

## ðŸ“„ 7. Policy Updates

Project Athlete 360 reserves the right to modify this billing policy at any time.  
Any changes will be notified via email and updated on the **Terms of Service** and **Pricing** pages.

